===Etymology===
{{NL.}} term ''[[anarchia]]'' < {{Gr.}} [[αναρχία]] < [[α-|αν-]] (without), + [[ἀρχός]] (ruler, authority).

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈænərki/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|anarchies|-}}

# The state of a society being without [[authoritarians]] or a governing body.
# A chaotic and confusing absence of any form of political [[authority]] or [[government]].

====Usage notes====
* Anarchists feel it is inappropriate to use the word “anarchy” to mean "a state of chaos or confusion". However, many non-anarchists do use it that way.

